 dog.speak();
// Output:
// 'Animal speaks'
// 'Dog barks'

`class` is a syntax introduced in ECMAScript 6 for creating objects and handling inheritance in JavaScript. It provides a more traditional and straightforward way to define object constructors and methods, similar to classes in other object-oriented languages. Classes use the `constructor` method to initialize objects and can extend other classes using the `extends` keyword. 

